Goal: Implement mergeDuplicates using TDD — write tests first, then implement

flow:
  prompt: Write at least 4 failing test cases in src/test.js for a mergeDuplicates(contacts) function. The function should merge contacts with the same email, keeping the most complete fields. Test cases should cover: basic merge, field priority, no-duplicates case, and multiple groups of duplicates. Do NOT implement the function yet.
  run: node src/test.js
  if command_succeeded
    prompt: Tests should be FAILING at this point since mergeDuplicates is not yet implemented. Make sure the tests actually call mergeDuplicates and will fail without an implementation.
  end
  prompt: Now implement the mergeDuplicates function in src/contacts.js. Export it. Make the minimal implementation to pass all the tests you just wrote.
  until command_succeeded max 5
    run: node src/test.js
    if command_failed
      prompt: Tests are still failing. Fix the implementation. Error output: ${last_stdout}
    end
  end

done when:
  file_exists src/contacts.js
